When one document may be updated frequently within very short period(a few updates within one second, for instance), the change stream event received by downstream processor may return the "fullDocument" that is inconsistent with the actual version when the update was applied to that document. To avoid this inconsistency, enable this option to store the full document along with the update operation. This will at the expense of additional storage and degraded performance.
